'''2011 reissue'''

In 2011, Warner Music Japan released the album as a [[Super Audio CD]] hybrid disc with "Silver Springs" as the sixth track, bumping "Songbird" to Track 12.

'''35th anniversary reissues'''

Warner Bros. and Rhino Entertainment marked the album's 35th anniversary by reissuing it in several formats <U+2013> a facsimile of the original on vinyl, without "Silver Springs", on 16 April 2011; a remastered CD, again without "Silver Springs", on 31 January 2012; and finally two box-sets on 29 January 2013.<ref>[http://www.rhino.com/article/the-rumours-are-true-fleetwood-mac-to-reissue-landmark-album "The Rumours Are True! Fleetwood Mac to Reissue Landmark Album"] and [http://www.rhino.com/article/fleetwood-mac-rumours-deluxe-and-expanded-editions-now-available "Fleetwood Mac Rumours Deluxe and Expanded Editions Now Available",] Rhino Records. Retrieved 21 March 2013.</ref>

The ''Expanded Edition'' on three CDs contains:
* the original album plus "Silver Springs"
* twelve previously unreleased live tracks recorded in 1977
* sixteen previously unreleased demos, roughs, and outtakes.

The ''Deluxe Edition'' (sometimes referred to as "super deluxe") on four CDs, one DVD, and one vinyl LP contains:
* the forty tracks in the expanded edition
* the eighteen demos, roughs, and outtakes included in the 2004 reissue
* ''The Rosebud Film'', a 1977 documentary by Michael Collins
* the original album on vinyl.

